# Sprint 3.1 – Phase 2 & 3: Walkthrough

This document outlines the implementation, test structure, and validation results for Sprint 3.1, covering the Security Layer (Phase 2) and Authentication Business Logic (Phase 3) for the AlgoPath application.

---

## What Was Implemented

### 1. Dependencies

* **[requirements.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements.txt)**: Added `bcrypt>=4.0.0` to secure production-ready password hashing.
* **[requirements-dev.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements-dev.txt)**: Created development dependencies file with `pytest>=8.0.0` for clean and isolated unit tests.

### 2. Centralized Dependencies

* **[dependencies.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/dependencies.py)**:
  * Centralized FastAPI dependency injection helpers `get_current_user` and `get_admin_user`.
  * Keeps the core service layer (`AuthService`, `JWTService`, `PasswordService`) 100% decoupled and free of FastAPI framework code (`Depends`, `HTTPException`, etc.).

### 3. Core Security Services

* **[password_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/password_service.py)**:
  * Stateless `PasswordService` with `hash_password(password)` and `verify_password(password, hashed_password)`.
  * Bypasses the deprecated `passlib` to interact directly with the modern `bcrypt` library.
* **[jwt_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/jwt_service.py)**:
  * Uses `python-jose` to manage JWT creation, verification, and decoding.
  * Encapsulates JWT errors into custom domains: `TokenExpiredError` and `TokenInvalidError`.
  * Restricts payloads strictly to `sub` and `exp`.

### 4. Authentication Business Logic

* **[auth_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/auth_service.py)**:
  * Completely refactored as a stateless orchestration layer.
  * Defines domain exceptions: `AuthenticationError`, `UserAlreadyExistsError`, `InvalidCredentialsError`, and `UserNotFoundError`.
  * Implemented a private `_normalize_email(email)` method to ensure uniform casing and spacing of emails.
  * `register_user(db, register_data) -> UserResponse`: Validates unique email, hashes password, creates user in DB, initializes progress records, and returns the sanitized Pydantic DTO. Safely rolls back the transaction (deleting the user) if progress initialization fails.
  * `login_user(db, login_data) -> TokenResponse`: Authenticates matching records and issues JWT. Uses identical `InvalidCredentialsError` details for both non-existent users and wrong passwords to block user enumeration.
  * `get_user_by_email(db, email) -> User` & `get_user_by_id(db, user_id) -> User`: Direct lookups that return the raw ORM `User` models for internal orchestration (satisfying user refinement requirements).

### 5. API Route Adjustments

* **[curriculum.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/routes/curriculum.py)**:
  * Refactored imports to reference `app.dependencies` for `get_current_user` instead of `app.services.auth_service`, adapting all routes seamlessly.

